1
00:00:00,001 --> 00:00:02,634
Julia:
<i>Chester's mill is a place</i>
<i>like any other.</i>

2
00:00:02,636 --> 00:00:04,636
<i>At least it used to be</i>

3
00:00:04,638 --> 00:00:07,740
<i>Until we were cut off</i>
<i>from the rest of the world</i>

4
00:00:07,742 --> 00:00:09,608
<i>By a mysterious dome.</i>

5
00:00:13,381 --> 00:00:16,048
<i>Invisible, indestructible,</i>

6
00:00:16,050 --> 00:00:17,616
<i>And completely inescapable.</i>

7
00:00:17,618 --> 00:00:19,618
We're trapped.

8
00:00:19,620 --> 00:00:22,321
Julia:
<i>We don't know where it</i>
<i>came from or why it's here,</i>

9
00:00:22,323 --> 00:00:24,590
<i>But now that we're all trapped</i>
<i>under the dome together,</i>

10
00:00:24,592 --> 00:00:26,291
<i>None of our secrets are safe.</i>

11
00:00:26,293 --> 00:00:27,393
Yesterday,

12
00:00:27,395 --> 00:00:29,228
Norrie and I, we found

13
00:00:29,230 --> 00:00:31,163
This... Egg

14
00:00:31,165 --> 00:00:32,598
With its own little
dome around it.

15
00:00:34,234 --> 00:00:36,168
The monarch will be crowned.

16
00:00:42,108 --> 00:00:44,376
You don't want to make
an enemy of me, barbie.

17
00:00:46,112 --> 00:00:49,281
There's two sides
to that coin, jim.

18
00:00:49,283 --> 00:00:52,818
What do you think of when I say
"the monarch will be crowned"?

19
00:00:52,820 --> 00:00:56,255
Uh... What are you
talking about?

20
00:00:56,823 --> 00:00:59,258
I wish I knew.

21
00:01:03,830 --> 00:01:06,331
It's not much further.

22
00:01:06,333 --> 00:01:08,233
You said it's an egg?

23
00:01:08,235 --> 00:01:10,069
With its own little
mini-dome around it?

24
00:01:10,071 --> 00:01:12,304
Yes, you've only
asked me 20 times.

25
00:01:12,306 --> 00:01:14,740
Well, you got to admit,
it sounds kind of out there.

26
00:01:14,742 --> 00:01:17,342
Yeah, I guess I
wouldn't believe it

27
00:01:17,344 --> 00:01:20,345
And joe thinks that
this thing could be

28
00:01:20,347 --> 00:01:22,147
What's powering the dome?

29
00:01:22,149 --> 00:01:24,249
Yeah, he just
didn't know how.

30
00:01:24,251 --> 00:01:25,384
You ever been
to a planetarium?

31
00:01:25,386 --> 00:01:26,652
Once in high school.

32
00:01:26,654 --> 00:01:27,786
Why?

33
00:01:27,788 --> 00:01:32,224
That egg is projecting the dome
around us the same way

34
00:01:32,226 --> 00:01:34,760
A planetarium projector
surrounds you with stars.

35
00:01:34,762 --> 00:01:36,862
Well, you're gonna get
to test that theory,

36
00:01:36,864 --> 00:01:39,131
'cause here it is.

37
00:01:43,837 --> 00:01:45,571
I don't see an egg.

38
00:01:58,218 --> 00:01:59,785
I am not crazy.

39
00:01:59,787 --> 00:02:01,787
It was clearly right here.

40
00:02:01,789 --> 00:02:04,156
Where'd it go?

41
00:02:04,158 --> 00:02:05,624
Linda:
Barbie, you around?

42
00:02:05,626 --> 00:02:07,526
Yeah, linda. Go ahead.

43
00:02:07,528 --> 00:02:09,528
Shots fired on greenway street.

44
00:02:09,530 --> 00:02:12,464
I need you here now.

45
00:02:12,466 --> 00:02:13,465
I'm on my way.

46
00:02:13,467 --> 00:02:14,900
I should go help.

47
00:02:14,902 --> 00:02:17,169
I have to find this thing.

48
00:02:17,171 --> 00:02:19,438
When you do, come find me.

49
00:02:20,707 --> 00:02:22,341
Joe:
Norrie?

50
00:02:22,343 --> 00:02:23,342
There's only one
rule when it comes

51
00:02:23,344 --> 00:02:24,276
To catching a chicken.

52
00:02:24,278 --> 00:02:25,277
Which is?

53
00:02:25,279 --> 00:02:27,379
It ain't easy.

54
00:02:27,381 --> 00:02:29,214
Yeah, but you have to kill it.

55
00:02:29,216 --> 00:02:30,782
I think they're
kind of cute.

56
00:02:33,454 --> 00:02:35,721
Okay, so when
your apparition told julia

57
00:02:35,723 --> 00:02:37,289
That the monarch
will be crowned,

58
00:02:37,291 --> 00:02:39,358
What do you think that means?

59
00:02:39,360 --> 00:02:42,361
Guess somebody in here
gets to be king.

60
00:02:42,363 --> 00:02:44,296
Or it could have something to do
with those monarch butterflies

61
00:02:44,298 --> 00:02:46,865
That were outside the dome
three days ago.

62
00:02:46,867 --> 00:02:49,368
Well, we should go back out
to that mini-dome.

63
00:02:49,370 --> 00:02:52,304
See if we can get your
apparition to explain himself.

64
00:02:52,306 --> 00:02:53,705
After we catch dinner.

65
00:02:55,909 --> 00:02:58,410
Good morning.

66
00:02:58,412 --> 00:03:00,546
Very good,
judging by that smile.

67
00:03:00,548 --> 00:03:03,515
Well, things are looking up
in this town.

68
00:03:03,517 --> 00:03:07,219
Yeah, I heard, uh, barbie got
the water flowing again.

69
00:03:07,221 --> 00:03:10,355
A lot of chester's millers
made that happen.

70
00:03:10,357 --> 00:03:12,324
And I just, uh, hammered out

71
00:03:12,326 --> 00:03:14,293
A food deal with our farmers.

72
00:03:14,295 --> 00:03:15,894
We barter goods and services

73
00:03:15,896 --> 00:03:18,463
For vegetables, meat.

74
00:03:18,465 --> 00:03:20,966
'cause I want
to keep this place open.

75
00:03:20,968 --> 00:03:22,868
Really?
Yeah.

76
00:03:22,870 --> 00:03:25,470
I know I can't run it
as good as rose did.

77
00:03:25,472 --> 00:03:28,907
Probably can't offer more
than one or two items a day.

78
00:03:28,909 --> 00:03:30,676
But I think it's important.

79
00:03:30,678 --> 00:03:33,946
Ah, so, from waitress to manager

80
00:03:33,948 --> 00:03:36,215
In a little over a week, huh?

81
00:03:37,383 --> 00:03:39,251
From waitress to owner.

82
00:03:40,253 --> 00:03:42,321
I want the deed, free and clear.

83
00:03:42,323 --> 00:03:44,723
For the first time in my life,
I want to be responsible

84
00:03:44,725 --> 00:03:46,758
For something.

85
00:03:46,760 --> 00:03:49,661
The only way to do that,
sink or swim,

86
00:03:49,663 --> 00:03:52,931
Is for it to be on me.

87
00:03:53,900 --> 00:03:56,335
Let me give it some thought.

88
00:03:56,337 --> 00:03:58,570
You do that.

89
00:04:01,007 --> 00:04:04,876
Hey.

90
00:04:04,878 --> 00:04:06,345
What happened?

91
00:04:06,347 --> 00:04:07,679
Is he okay?

92
00:04:07,681 --> 00:04:09,014
By pure luck.

93
00:04:09,016 --> 00:04:12,017
The bullet only
grazed him.

94
00:04:12,019 --> 00:04:13,752
So who fired the shot?

95
00:04:13,754 --> 00:04:15,754
His neighbor,
ted utley.

96
00:04:15,756 --> 00:04:17,422
And I'd do it again.
Barbie:
Whoa. Whoa, whoa,

97
00:04:17,424 --> 00:04:18,557
Whoa, whoa.
I'm sorry about

98
00:04:18,559 --> 00:04:20,292
Mr. Feldman.
I wasn't shooting at him.

99
00:04:20,294 --> 00:04:23,662
My property. And that freak,
he was banging on my door.

100
00:04:23,664 --> 00:04:26,431
What freak?
At my house.
He's still inside.

101
00:04:26,433 --> 00:04:28,300
Weird-looking guy showed up,
ranting that he had to hide

102
00:04:28,302 --> 00:04:29,835
From the voices coming
from the dome.

103
00:04:29,837 --> 00:04:31,837
I said I had a gun,
but he wouldn't leave,

104
00:04:31,839 --> 00:04:33,772
So I fired off a couple shots
to scare him off.

105
00:04:33,774 --> 00:04:35,440
Except you hit your neighbor.
And that freak

106
00:04:35,442 --> 00:04:36,642
Didn't even run off.

107
00:04:36,644 --> 00:04:38,377
This thing started off
by killing people,

108
00:04:38,379 --> 00:04:40,812
And now it's just driving
the rest of us crazy.

109
00:04:40,814 --> 00:04:42,481
You know, we're all
gonna die in here.

110
00:04:42,483 --> 00:04:43,815
Just calm down, mr. Utley, okay?

111
00:04:43,817 --> 00:04:45,550
We're gonna go get the guy
out of your house.

112
00:04:45,552 --> 00:04:47,986
Preferably without anyone else
getting shot.

113
00:04:51,858 --> 00:04:54,293
Stop talking to me, dome!

114
00:04:54,295 --> 00:04:56,962
Get out! I need quiet!

115
00:04:56,964 --> 00:04:58,530
Get down!
Get back!
Let me see your hands!

116
00:04:58,532 --> 00:05:00,432
Let me see your hands! Get down!
Please don't hurt me!

117
00:05:00,434 --> 00:05:02,567
Hands behind your head.
I just got
to stop the voices!

118
00:05:02,569 --> 00:05:05,404
Larry?
You know this guy?

119
00:05:05,406 --> 00:05:07,673
Yeah, I've busted him
a million times for drugs.

120
00:05:07,675 --> 00:05:11,443
Oh, so it's not the dome talking
to you, is it? It's the drugs.

121
00:05:12,779 --> 00:05:15,447
Yeah, what is it this time,
larry? Meth? Crack?

122
00:05:15,449 --> 00:05:16,615
Rapture.

123
00:05:18,418 --> 00:05:20,085
Never heard of it.

124
00:05:20,087 --> 00:05:22,487
It's like every
kind of high combined.

125
00:05:22,489 --> 00:05:24,890
Coggins promised it'd
be like seeing heaven.

126
00:05:24,892 --> 00:05:27,459
The-the preacher sold you drugs?

127
00:05:27,461 --> 00:05:29,561
Yes, right there
at his funeral home.

128
00:05:29,563 --> 00:05:30,762
I need more!

129
00:05:36,502 --> 00:05:38,737
Hi, ange.
Get the hell out of here.

130
00:05:38,739 --> 00:05:40,772
Please, I'm not gonna hurt you.
I just...

131
00:05:40,774 --> 00:05:42,674
Wanted
something to eat.
No, junior. No.

132
00:05:43,476 --> 00:05:45,010
This is my place now,

133
00:05:45,012 --> 00:05:47,612
And I reserve the right
to refuse service to anyone,

134
00:05:47,614 --> 00:05:49,614
Especially psychos who chain up
their ex-girlfriends.

135
00:05:49,616 --> 00:05:52,351
I only did that because the
dome was making you sick.

136
00:05:52,353 --> 00:05:54,920
I'm not sick, junior.

137
00:05:54,922 --> 00:05:57,089
The dome has nothing
to do with me.

138
00:06:00,493 --> 00:06:02,427
Angie.

139
00:06:02,429 --> 00:06:03,128
Angie!

140
00:06:03,130 --> 00:06:04,796
The pink stars are falling.

141
00:06:04,798 --> 00:06:06,732
The pink stars
are falling in lines.

142
00:06:07,900 --> 00:06:09,668
The pink stars are falling.

143
00:06:28,488 --> 00:06:29,821
You got one second to tell me

144
00:06:29,823 --> 00:06:31,690
Why I shouldn't
blow your damn head off.

145
00:06:35,528 --> 00:06:38,096
Because you don't want
to ruin this beautiful face?

146
00:06:43,469 --> 00:06:45,570
Hi, jimmy.

147
00:07:06,426 --> 00:07:08,760
Let me out!
Angie, angie...

148
00:07:08,762 --> 00:07:11,496
help!
Angie, relax.

149
00:07:11,498 --> 00:07:14,566
Calm down, okay? You're safe!
somebody help me!

150
00:07:14,568 --> 00:07:17,169
- You're safe.
- until what?

151
00:07:17,171 --> 00:07:20,005
Until you lock me
into the fallout shelter again?

152
00:07:20,007 --> 00:07:21,206
You had a seizure.

153
00:07:21,208 --> 00:07:23,008
You kept saying:
"pink stars are falling."

154
00:07:23,010 --> 00:07:25,510
I only put you back there
to keep you safe.

155
00:07:25,512 --> 00:07:29,147
And I took care of you.
Like I am now.

156
00:07:29,149 --> 00:07:31,149
See?
I brought you home.

157
00:07:39,126 --> 00:07:41,493
You're really letting me go?

158
00:07:43,763 --> 00:07:46,498
I think I'll see you again.

159
00:07:47,533 --> 00:07:50,135
The mini-dome's gone?

160
00:07:50,137 --> 00:07:53,605
Just a pile of leaves
and a hole in the ground.

161
00:07:53,607 --> 00:07:55,106
You guys didn't move it,
did you?

162
00:07:55,108 --> 00:07:57,142
No. Why would we?

163
00:07:57,144 --> 00:07:59,144
I don't know,
but we need to find it again.

164
00:07:59,146 --> 00:08:02,481
I just wish my mom was
still here to help us.

165
00:08:02,483 --> 00:08:04,883
I can't believe she was
alive just two days ago.

166
00:08:05,852 --> 00:08:07,552
How's carolyn doing?

167
00:08:07,554 --> 00:08:08,954
She's still grieving.

168
00:08:08,956 --> 00:08:10,622
Should you stay with her?

169
00:08:10,624 --> 00:08:13,625
We had a long talk
this morning, and...

170
00:08:13,627 --> 00:08:17,229
She said she just needs
some time alone.

171
00:08:17,231 --> 00:08:19,898
And I need to do this.

172
00:08:19,900 --> 00:08:22,501
hey.

173
00:08:22,503 --> 00:08:26,271
joe:
Angie.

174
00:08:26,273 --> 00:08:29,040
You...
Look like crap.

175
00:08:29,042 --> 00:08:31,243
Thanks.

176
00:08:31,245 --> 00:08:34,112
I just had a seizure
at the diner.

177
00:08:34,114 --> 00:08:36,581
What do you mean
you had a seizure?

178
00:08:36,583 --> 00:08:38,917
Angie:
I mean I was just standing
there and then I...

179
00:08:38,919 --> 00:08:42,254
I went blank and... Collapsed.

180
00:08:42,256 --> 00:08:44,122
Did you say, "the pink
stars are falling"?

181
00:08:45,091 --> 00:08:46,892
How did you know that?

182
00:08:46,894 --> 00:08:49,961
Because norrie and I have had
the exact same seizure.

183
00:08:49,963 --> 00:08:51,830
What? Why didn't you tell me?

184
00:08:51,832 --> 00:08:53,999
You haven't exactly
been here a lot.

185
00:08:54,001 --> 00:08:55,600
Oh, my god.

186
00:08:55,602 --> 00:08:56,234
Angie...

187
00:08:56,236 --> 00:08:58,103
junior's right.

188
00:08:58,105 --> 00:09:00,171
I <i>am</i> sick.

189
00:09:01,807 --> 00:09:05,076
Julia:
Honey, why don't you
sit down for a minute?

190
00:09:05,078 --> 00:09:08,713
No, I need to get
a glass of water first.

191
00:09:12,718 --> 00:09:15,186
Joe...

192
00:09:15,188 --> 00:09:17,789
Did you know that angie
has a butterfly tattoo?

193
00:09:17,791 --> 00:09:20,725
Yeah. My parents almost
killed her when she got it.

194
00:09:20,727 --> 00:09:22,761
And now she's having seizures.

195
00:09:22,763 --> 00:09:25,163
Maybe she's the monarch
who will be crowned.

196
00:09:25,165 --> 00:09:27,766
My sister? No way.

197
00:09:27,768 --> 00:09:29,301
And monarch butterflies
are orange.

198
00:09:29,303 --> 00:09:31,703
Angie's is blue and yellow,

199
00:09:31,705 --> 00:09:33,238
So there goes that theory.

200
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:34,906
Well, the only way
we're gonna get answers

201
00:09:34,908 --> 00:09:36,641
Is if we find the mini-dome.

202
00:09:36,643 --> 00:09:38,677
What about that contraption
that dodee made--

203
00:09:38,679 --> 00:09:40,078
The yagi?

204
00:09:40,080 --> 00:09:41,947
It locates energy
sources, right?

205
00:09:41,949 --> 00:09:44,683
Yeah. If the egg's
what's powering the dome

206
00:09:44,685 --> 00:09:46,952
Then the yagi might help us
track it down.

207
00:09:46,954 --> 00:09:48,653
Let's ask her to borrow it.

208
00:09:48,655 --> 00:09:50,322
Dodee got a little weird
the last time

209
00:09:50,324 --> 00:09:51,923
She was around the two of you.

210
00:09:51,925 --> 00:09:53,725
Better let me go talk to her.

211
00:09:57,830 --> 00:09:59,898
Big jim at a loss for words.

212
00:09:59,900 --> 00:10:02,901
Never thought I'd see the day.

213
00:10:02,903 --> 00:10:04,135
What are you doing here, max?

214
00:10:05,237 --> 00:10:08,173
I can't just drop in
on an old friend?

215
00:10:09,141 --> 00:10:10,842
I mean inside the dome.

216
00:10:12,378 --> 00:10:14,012
Did you get through it somehow?

217
00:10:14,014 --> 00:10:17,349
Like I would try
and break in? Please.

218
00:10:17,351 --> 00:10:20,819
No. I don't like being in
this crappy town on a good day.

219
00:10:21,787 --> 00:10:23,755
So you got trapped.
The one day

220
00:10:23,757 --> 00:10:26,091
I decide to leave westlake
to come see you

221
00:10:26,093 --> 00:10:29,327
And that thing just...
Comes down out of nowhere.

222
00:10:29,329 --> 00:10:31,896
You were coming to see me?
Yeah, I kept hearing

223
00:10:31,898 --> 00:10:34,032
About problems
with our little arrangement.

224
00:10:34,034 --> 00:10:36,768
The one you assured me
you had under control?

225
00:10:36,770 --> 00:10:38,403
Which I did.

226
00:10:38,405 --> 00:10:41,640
So... Duke perkins
<i>wasn't</i> getting antsy

227
00:10:41,642 --> 00:10:43,174
About looking the other way?

228
00:10:43,176 --> 00:10:45,877
And the wacko preacher <i>wasn't</i>
<i>making up his own batches</i>

229
00:10:45,879 --> 00:10:47,045
Of our product?

230
00:10:47,047 --> 00:10:50,315
Rapture... Is <i>your</i> product, max.

231
00:10:50,317 --> 00:10:52,717
Which I never could
have gotten off the ground

232
00:10:52,719 --> 00:10:54,853
Without you and your supply
of my secret ingredient.

233
00:10:54,855 --> 00:10:57,222
Duke and coggins
aren't a problem anymore,

234
00:10:57,224 --> 00:10:58,990
So you can relax.

235
00:11:02,862 --> 00:11:05,430
And, uh...

236
00:11:05,432 --> 00:11:08,900
If you got caught in here
like the rest of us...

237
00:11:08,902 --> 00:11:10,135
Where the hell you been

238
00:11:10,137 --> 00:11:11,903
The last eight days?

239
00:11:11,905 --> 00:11:13,805
I found a house.
The people who are

240
00:11:13,807 --> 00:11:15,807
Living there, they got
caught outside the dome--

241
00:11:15,809 --> 00:11:17,442
Lucky bastards--
and, um...

242
00:11:17,444 --> 00:11:19,444
Been there.

243
00:11:19,446 --> 00:11:21,813
Hoping that someone
would free us from
this nightmare,

244
00:11:21,815 --> 00:11:24,849
And when that didn't
happen, I...
You...

245
00:11:24,851 --> 00:11:27,285
Decided to make the best
of a bad situation.

246
00:11:28,355 --> 00:11:30,855
You know me
so well, jimmy.

247
00:11:30,857 --> 00:11:32,857
What's that expression?

248
00:11:32,859 --> 00:11:35,360
Uh, "never let a good
crisis go to waste"?

249
00:11:35,362 --> 00:11:37,996
: Well, I
would say chester's mill

250
00:11:37,998 --> 00:11:39,898
Is in more than
a crisis, so...

251
00:11:39,900 --> 00:11:41,800
You and I need
to get to work.

252
00:11:41,802 --> 00:11:44,869
And you're the man
to make it happen.

253
00:11:52,011 --> 00:11:54,345
I'm not sure
I've ever seen a town

254
00:11:54,347 --> 00:11:57,382
Where the preacher
was also the mortician.

255
00:11:57,384 --> 00:11:58,850
Reverend coggins always said

256
00:11:58,852 --> 00:12:01,019
He ran a one-stop
"body and soul" shop.

257
00:12:01,021 --> 00:12:03,088
So let's see what
he left behind.

258
00:12:12,198 --> 00:12:14,199
I really can't believe this.

259
00:12:14,201 --> 00:12:15,800
What, that coggins

260
00:12:15,802 --> 00:12:17,402
Was making drugs?

261
00:12:17,404 --> 00:12:20,171
I've known him
since I was a little kid.

262
00:12:20,173 --> 00:12:22,440
Well, he was probably
taking them, too.

263
00:12:22,442 --> 00:12:26,044
Guy seemed high as a kite
every time I met him.

264
00:12:26,046 --> 00:12:28,146
This is the recipe
he was using.

265
00:12:28,148 --> 00:12:30,915
Denatured alcohol,
chemical stabilizers...

266
00:12:30,917 --> 00:12:33,118
Liquid propane.

267
00:12:35,187 --> 00:12:38,389
I've never heard of that
being used to make drugs.

268
00:12:38,391 --> 00:12:40,492
Well, still, if
you need propane,

269
00:12:40,494 --> 00:12:44,229
This town seems to have
a hell of a lot of it.

270
00:12:48,267 --> 00:12:51,436
This one goes out to wybs's
regular deejay, phil bushey,

271
00:12:51,438 --> 00:12:54,539
Who was dumb enough
to try and stop a bullet

272
00:12:54,541 --> 00:12:56,541
With his shoulder yesterday.

273
00:12:56,543 --> 00:12:59,010
Feel better, philly.

274
00:12:59,012 --> 00:13:01,079
Holding down
the fort, huh?

275
00:13:01,081 --> 00:13:06,184
I also send out an all-bandwidth
sos every three hours, but...

276
00:13:06,186 --> 00:13:09,053
Let me guess-- no word
from the outside world.

277
00:13:09,055 --> 00:13:10,789
Not even a peep.

278
00:13:10,791 --> 00:13:13,424
So, what are you up to?

279
00:13:13,426 --> 00:13:17,028
I was wondering if I
could borrow the yagi
for a couple hours.

280
00:13:17,030 --> 00:13:18,997
Why?

281
00:13:18,999 --> 00:13:20,799
Dome has to
have some kind

282
00:13:20,801 --> 00:13:22,100
Of power source.

283
00:13:22,102 --> 00:13:24,002
Thought I'd take another
shot at wandering around,

284
00:13:24,004 --> 00:13:25,904
See if anything
makes it ping.

285
00:13:25,906 --> 00:13:28,106
I know,
it's a long shot,

286
00:13:28,108 --> 00:13:30,008
But it's still better
than nothing, right?

287
00:13:30,010 --> 00:13:31,976
The yagi's not gonna help you,

288
00:13:31,978 --> 00:13:34,112
'cause it stopped working
after joe and norrie

289
00:13:34,114 --> 00:13:35,980
Touched the dome
the other day.

290
00:13:35,982 --> 00:13:37,549
Really?
Yeah. It's another
freaky thing

291
00:13:37,551 --> 00:13:39,083
That happened
because of them.

292
00:13:39,085 --> 00:13:41,286
Wait, this wasn't
their idea, was it?

293
00:13:41,288 --> 00:13:45,190
No, this one's all me.
Good, 'cause I still
don't trust those two.

294
00:13:45,192 --> 00:13:47,892
Have you told
anyone else that?
No.

295
00:13:47,894 --> 00:13:50,128
Like I promised I wouldn't.
Look, are we done here?

296
00:13:50,130 --> 00:13:53,898
'cause I've got a
lot of work to do.
Yeah, sure.

297
00:13:53,900 --> 00:13:56,968
Thanks, anyway.

298
00:14:00,372 --> 00:14:02,440
Heard you had a shooting.

299
00:14:04,009 --> 00:14:07,145
A junkie broke in to
ted utley's house
and he shot at him.

300
00:14:07,147 --> 00:14:08,847
Luckily no one
was seriously hurt.

301
00:14:08,849 --> 00:14:10,481
Hope we can say that next time.

302
00:14:10,483 --> 00:14:11,549
Next time?

303
00:14:11,551 --> 00:14:13,518
Someone opens fire.

304
00:14:13,520 --> 00:14:15,520
You know it's gonna happen.

305
00:14:15,522 --> 00:14:19,924
I've been thinking--
a lot of folks have
guns in our town.

306
00:14:19,926 --> 00:14:23,161
The only reason ollie was able
to cut us off from his well

307
00:14:23,163 --> 00:14:26,030
Was because he and his crew
were armed to the teeth.

308
00:14:26,032 --> 00:14:28,566
So what are you saying,
we collect all the guns?

309
00:14:28,568 --> 00:14:32,170
We might want to think about it.

310
00:14:33,939 --> 00:14:37,041
Jim, people have
a constitutional
right to bear arms.

311
00:14:37,043 --> 00:14:38,409
<i>If</i> we're still
a part of america.

312
00:14:38,411 --> 00:14:39,944
Of course we are.
Really?

313
00:14:39,946 --> 00:14:42,180
With that dome cutting
us off, I'd say we're

314
00:14:42,182 --> 00:14:44,315
Looking more like
our own country every day.

315
00:14:44,317 --> 00:14:45,383
I mean, resources

316
00:14:45,385 --> 00:14:47,151
Are only gonna
get scarcer,

317
00:14:47,153 --> 00:14:49,020
Tensions aren't going down
anytime soon...

318
00:14:49,022 --> 00:14:50,889
That's only gonna raise it more.

319
00:14:50,891 --> 00:14:52,423
Look, I know it's
gonna be controversial,

320
00:14:52,425 --> 00:14:54,425
But what's the harm
in proposing the idea?

321
00:14:54,427 --> 00:14:56,060
I mean,
come on, barbie,

322
00:14:56,062 --> 00:14:58,129
You saw neighbor
turn against neighbor in iraq--

323
00:14:58,131 --> 00:15:00,565
It's never pretty.
So let's not

324
00:15:00,567 --> 00:15:03,001
Have that happen here.

325
00:15:03,003 --> 00:15:05,570
I go on the radio,
I float the idea--

326
00:15:05,572 --> 00:15:08,473
It's a totally
voluntary program.

327
00:15:08,475 --> 00:15:12,176
I mean, hell, mine... Mine's
the first on the stack.

328
00:15:15,114 --> 00:15:16,414
All right.

329
00:15:16,416 --> 00:15:19,317
As long as it's voluntary
and temporary.

330
00:15:19,319 --> 00:15:21,953
But the moment
this dome comes down...

331
00:15:21,955 --> 00:15:25,223
People get their guns back.
Course.

332
00:15:25,225 --> 00:15:27,425
You're gonna need help
making that happen, so...

333
00:15:27,427 --> 00:15:29,961
That should be me.

334
00:15:29,963 --> 00:15:32,964
Only if I can count on you.

335
00:15:32,966 --> 00:15:36,034
You made the sale,
jim, so... Let's go.

336
00:15:44,576 --> 00:15:46,978
You really on board with this?

337
00:15:46,980 --> 00:15:48,546
Hell, no, but I'm
gonna stay close to him;

338
00:15:48,548 --> 00:15:50,248
I want to see what he's up to.

339
00:15:56,957 --> 00:16:02,093
This is councilman
jim rennie with a very
important public message.

340
00:16:02,095 --> 00:16:05,563
Folks, I need your help
to make our streets safer

341
00:16:05,565 --> 00:16:07,699
And our citizens more secure.

342
00:16:07,701 --> 00:16:11,102
I'm starting
a firearm turn-in program.

343
00:16:11,104 --> 00:16:14,005
This program is
completely voluntary.

344
00:16:14,007 --> 00:16:15,473
No one's coming to your home.

345
00:16:15,475 --> 00:16:19,110
This is just a way for all of us
to show each other that

346
00:16:19,112 --> 00:16:21,679
No one means
anybody else any harm.

347
00:16:21,681 --> 00:16:24,148
And of course...

348
00:16:24,150 --> 00:16:26,384
As soon as this
crisis is over,

349
00:16:26,386 --> 00:16:28,386
You all get your guns back.

350
00:16:28,388 --> 00:16:30,755
And as a reward,
anyone who participates

351
00:16:30,757 --> 00:16:33,024
Will get extra food,

352
00:16:33,026 --> 00:16:34,525
Extra propane.

353
00:16:34,527 --> 00:16:36,761
So come on down
to the sweetbriar diner,

354
00:16:36,763 --> 00:16:38,262
And bring your rifles,

355
00:16:38,264 --> 00:16:40,498
Your handguns, your ammo,
whatever you got.

356
00:16:40,500 --> 00:16:43,001
And remember, as always...

357
00:16:43,003 --> 00:16:46,371
We'll get through this...
Just as long

358
00:16:46,373 --> 00:16:48,606
As we all pull together.

359
00:16:55,014 --> 00:16:57,181
And this is me
on my first birthday.

360
00:16:57,183 --> 00:17:00,051
Cute.
Dressed up
for my cousin's wedding.

361
00:17:00,053 --> 00:17:03,287
Aw, sweet.
Oh, I didn't mean
to put that one in there.

362
00:17:03,289 --> 00:17:06,090
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
go back to that one.
You're shirtless.

363
00:17:06,092 --> 00:17:08,059
Let's see those
abs of yours.

364
00:17:08,061 --> 00:17:09,093
Moving on.

365
00:17:11,630 --> 00:17:13,364
Hey, guys.

366
00:17:14,767 --> 00:17:16,501
Where's the yagi?

367
00:17:16,503 --> 00:17:19,437
Broken... If dodee
is to be believed.

368
00:17:19,439 --> 00:17:22,573
Either way, we need another
way to find the mini-dome.

369
00:17:22,575 --> 00:17:24,175
We could go door-to-door.

370
00:17:24,177 --> 00:17:26,477
: Ask anyone if
they went out for a walk

371
00:17:26,479 --> 00:17:30,415
And happened to bring back
a mysterious orb the size
of a beach ball.

372
00:17:31,383 --> 00:17:33,384
Or we could use his nose.

373
00:17:33,386 --> 00:17:36,287
He sensed the mini-dome
before we could even see it,

374
00:17:36,289 --> 00:17:37,488
And started growling.

375
00:17:39,258 --> 00:17:42,427
Maybe he'll do it again.

376
00:17:42,429 --> 00:17:44,662
Come on, we're taking a drive.

377
00:17:44,664 --> 00:17:47,198
Where to, boss?
Propane warehouse.

378
00:17:47,200 --> 00:17:49,667
Reverend coggins was using
that stuff to make drugs.

379
00:17:49,669 --> 00:17:52,203
Junior.

380
00:17:52,205 --> 00:17:56,474
Uh... Sorry, but do
you mind if I don't go
with you on this one?

381
00:17:56,476 --> 00:17:59,677
You can't just bug out
on the job whenever
you feel like it.
I know,

382
00:17:59,679 --> 00:18:01,345
But this is important.

383
00:18:01,347 --> 00:18:02,680
Angie...

384
00:18:04,383 --> 00:18:06,217
...Needs my help.

385
00:18:06,219 --> 00:18:07,552
Keep your radio on.

386
00:18:07,554 --> 00:18:08,820
Thanks, linda.

387
00:18:11,757 --> 00:18:14,459
I knew you'd come find me.

388
00:18:14,461 --> 00:18:18,696
Why have you always said that
the dome is making me sick?

389
00:18:18,698 --> 00:18:20,531
Because it's true.

390
00:18:20,533 --> 00:18:23,768
So you've locked me up?
In the bomb shelter,
to keep you safe.

391
00:18:23,770 --> 00:18:26,137
But now you're out
and you're even sicker.

392
00:18:26,139 --> 00:18:27,705
But there's more,

393
00:18:27,707 --> 00:18:28,840
Isn't there?

394
00:18:28,842 --> 00:18:30,241
Yeah.

395
00:18:30,243 --> 00:18:32,410
But I didn't realize it
until this morning,

396
00:18:32,412 --> 00:18:35,313
When you had a seizure
and started talking
about pink stars.

397
00:18:35,315 --> 00:18:37,181
What about them?

398
00:18:37,183 --> 00:18:39,617
Come on. I want
to show you something.

399
00:18:45,758 --> 00:18:47,592
Okay, I'm coming.

400
00:18:47,594 --> 00:18:49,627
Much appreciated,
mr. Danbury.

401
00:18:49,629 --> 00:18:51,662
Come down for
some extra propane.

402
00:18:51,664 --> 00:18:53,364
Thank you, sir.

403
00:18:53,366 --> 00:18:55,566
Big jim: I can't believe
how many of our gun owners

404
00:18:55,568 --> 00:18:58,603
Showed up already,
and on such short notice.

405
00:18:58,605 --> 00:19:01,472
Big jim talks,
and people listen.
They do

406
00:19:01,474 --> 00:19:03,174
When it's the right idea.

407
00:19:05,344 --> 00:19:07,311
Here you go, jim.

408
00:19:07,313 --> 00:19:10,281
Hey, listen, if you see
ted utley, tell him

409
00:19:10,283 --> 00:19:13,918
I was hoping to see him
down here today.
Well, I saw him earlier.

410
00:19:13,920 --> 00:19:17,688
He said you'll have to kill him
before he gives up his guns.

411
00:19:21,927 --> 00:19:24,395
Damn it.

412
00:19:29,369 --> 00:19:31,202
Hey, a guy like utley,

413
00:19:31,204 --> 00:19:32,837
You knew he was
never gonna comply.

414
00:19:32,839 --> 00:19:35,206
Ted has always been
a gun collector.

415
00:19:35,208 --> 00:19:37,441
He hasn't always
been wound so tight.

416
00:19:37,443 --> 00:19:39,844
Until the dome came down.

417
00:19:39,846 --> 00:19:42,446
His wife was driving
their kid to camp.

418
00:19:42,448 --> 00:19:45,917
Smashed right into it;
both of them died.

419
00:19:45,919 --> 00:19:48,452
Been worried about him
ever since.

420
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:03,534
The man's clearly
troubled, barbie.

421
00:20:03,536 --> 00:20:05,970
Whatever happened
to "we're not coming
into your homes,

422
00:20:05,972 --> 00:20:08,306
This is a voluntary program"?

423
00:20:08,308 --> 00:20:09,440
: Yeah.

424
00:20:09,442 --> 00:20:11,242
Ted's gone cuckoo.

425
00:20:11,244 --> 00:20:13,311
It might be necessary.

426
00:20:15,514 --> 00:20:17,582
Hey, jim...

427
00:20:20,986 --> 00:20:24,555
If he's so cuckoo, you're
gonna need some backup.

428
00:20:30,662 --> 00:20:32,496
Come on, truman,
where is it?

429
00:20:32,498 --> 00:20:34,532
Where's the mini-dome?

430
00:20:34,534 --> 00:20:36,834
He's too busy showing us
the best places to pee.

431
00:20:36,836 --> 00:20:38,803
What if it didn't move,

432
00:20:38,805 --> 00:20:41,005
And it just disappeared?

433
00:20:41,007 --> 00:20:43,307
Maybe we hallucinated it.

434
00:20:43,309 --> 00:20:47,411
Things don't just disappear
into thin air.
Norrie: Really?

435
00:20:47,413 --> 00:20:50,414
Just like things don't just
<i>appear out</i> of thin air

436
00:20:50,416 --> 00:20:51,749
And swallow towns whole.

437
00:20:51,751 --> 00:20:54,418
There is a rational
explanation for this.

438
00:20:54,420 --> 00:20:55,553
Okay? For all of this.

439
00:20:55,555 --> 00:20:57,755
There has to be;
we just have to find it.

440
00:21:01,594 --> 00:21:05,263
Good boy, truman.
That's it, that's it.

441
00:21:13,305 --> 00:21:15,673
Great. Birds.

442
00:21:15,675 --> 00:21:18,009
Come on. Let's keep going.

443
00:21:26,286 --> 00:21:27,885
About time the cops decided

444
00:21:27,887 --> 00:21:30,721
To see what's going
on with this place.

445
00:21:30,723 --> 00:21:33,391
I saw you drive up
from my porch over there.

446
00:21:33,393 --> 00:21:36,027
I seen a lot of suspicious
things from that porch.

447
00:21:36,029 --> 00:21:38,996
Like?
Boomer's truck blow
up the other day.

448
00:21:38,998 --> 00:21:41,599
Oh, but that was an accident.
He was smoking.

449
00:21:41,601 --> 00:21:43,634
Lot of other trucks
coming and going, too,

450
00:21:43,636 --> 00:21:46,504
The past couple of months.
People here day and night.

451
00:21:46,506 --> 00:21:49,440
And why's our town
stockpiling all this propane

452
00:21:49,442 --> 00:21:50,908
In the first place?

453
00:21:50,910 --> 00:21:53,644
Seems awfully convenient
once that dome came down.

454
00:21:53,646 --> 00:21:55,513
Why didn't you come and tell me?

455
00:21:55,515 --> 00:21:57,748
I told our former sheriff,

456
00:21:57,750 --> 00:22:00,084
God rest his soul.
Duke knew about this?

457
00:22:02,421 --> 00:22:04,055
Maybe it just slipped his mind.

458
00:22:04,057 --> 00:22:06,490
Or he didn't
want you to know.

459
00:22:06,492 --> 00:22:08,693
When I called him,
he just about hung up on me.

460
00:22:08,695 --> 00:22:11,095
Never heard the man
sound so nervous.

461
00:22:15,701 --> 00:22:18,703
Go talk to julia shumway.

462
00:22:18,705 --> 00:22:21,672
She'll tell you I said
something here was fishy.

463
00:22:52,371 --> 00:22:54,105
You didn't have to come.

464
00:22:54,107 --> 00:22:56,474
I'm going in to talk
to ted utley.

465
00:22:56,476 --> 00:22:58,409
Make your way around the side,
see if you can

466
00:22:58,411 --> 00:23:00,578
Find a window
and get a bead on him.

467
00:23:00,580 --> 00:23:01,812
But do not fire

468
00:23:01,814 --> 00:23:03,681
Unless things
go sideways.

469
00:23:06,818 --> 00:23:08,753
That sideways enough for you?

470
00:23:21,066 --> 00:23:23,601
Don't worry, angie,
I promised you

471
00:23:23,603 --> 00:23:26,704
And my dad I'd never hold you
against your will again.

472
00:23:26,706 --> 00:23:28,506
But where are you taking me?

473
00:23:29,474 --> 00:23:31,509
Right over here.

474
00:23:32,477 --> 00:23:33,944
Your mom's studio?

475
00:23:55,734 --> 00:23:59,203
Seems like yesterday
she was in here.

476
00:23:59,205 --> 00:24:02,673
Not nine years ago.

477
00:24:05,677 --> 00:24:08,045
She loved making art.

478
00:24:08,047 --> 00:24:10,514
I remember.

479
00:24:10,516 --> 00:24:13,751
I took her pottery class
in junior high.

480
00:24:15,787 --> 00:24:17,855
But what does any of this have
to do with my seizure?

481
00:24:17,857 --> 00:24:21,192
A couple months before she died,
she had this dream about me,

482
00:24:21,194 --> 00:24:24,862
And she... Woke up,
she came out here

483
00:24:24,864 --> 00:24:28,532
And she just started painting
this as fast as she could.

484
00:24:33,705 --> 00:24:36,707
Now, in her dream,

485
00:24:36,709 --> 00:24:38,776
I was on this hill...

486
00:24:40,946 --> 00:24:43,013
...Looking up at these.

487
00:24:51,790 --> 00:24:53,858
Pink stars.

488
00:24:56,862 --> 00:24:58,929
Ted?

489
00:25:00,065 --> 00:25:02,867
It is jim rennie.

490
00:25:02,869 --> 00:25:06,804
I'm coming in,

491
00:25:06,806 --> 00:25:09,006
So you're gonna put
that gun down.

492
00:25:09,008 --> 00:25:11,075
Got that?

493
00:25:11,077 --> 00:25:13,277
Ted:
Yeah.

494
00:25:13,279 --> 00:25:16,280
Big jim:
I'm guessing that
shot at my car...

495
00:25:16,282 --> 00:25:19,216
Was a misfire

496
00:25:19,218 --> 00:25:22,286
'cause I know you, ted.

497
00:25:23,221 --> 00:25:25,789
You're no killer.

498
00:25:30,128 --> 00:25:32,796
Expecting that gun to be down.

499
00:25:38,103 --> 00:25:40,237
Good.

500
00:25:40,239 --> 00:25:42,873
Now I'm gonna put my gun away...

501
00:25:43,975 --> 00:25:46,911
...And you and I are gonna talk.

502
00:26:17,309 --> 00:26:20,010
What's going on, ted?

503
00:26:21,947 --> 00:26:23,847
I can't do it, jim.

504
00:26:23,849 --> 00:26:25,249
Turn in your firearms, you mean?

505
00:26:29,788 --> 00:26:31,055
That dome's
already taken

506
00:26:31,057 --> 00:26:32,856
Enough from me.

507
00:26:32,858 --> 00:26:35,059
I know.

508
00:26:35,061 --> 00:26:37,127
Janice and scott.

509
00:26:37,129 --> 00:26:39,029
I'm not giving up
one more thing.

510
00:26:48,807 --> 00:26:50,040
Ted, listen to me.

511
00:26:56,348 --> 00:26:57,982
I know how you're feeling.

512
00:26:57,984 --> 00:26:59,683
Okay? I lost

513
00:26:59,685 --> 00:27:02,152
Pauline out of the blue,
nine years ago.

514
00:27:02,154 --> 00:27:06,256
There's not a day that goes by
where she isn't on my mind.

515
00:27:06,258 --> 00:27:09,627
It'll get better,
I promise you.

516
00:27:14,699 --> 00:27:16,333
I'm sorry, jim.

517
00:27:16,335 --> 00:27:18,335
But there's nothing here
for me anymore.

518
00:27:20,805 --> 00:27:21,372
No!

519
00:27:32,051 --> 00:27:35,653
See if they can sedate
him for the night.

520
00:27:35,655 --> 00:27:37,254
Let's go back there and
pack up those firearms,

521
00:27:37,256 --> 00:27:38,389
Get 'em ready to go.

522
00:27:39,357 --> 00:27:41,959
Will do.

523
00:27:41,961 --> 00:27:43,961
Listen, barbie,
I could practically feel

524
00:27:43,963 --> 00:27:46,096
That red dot on the
back of my head so...

525
00:27:46,098 --> 00:27:50,167
Glad you kept your cool and
didn't accidentally ice me.

526
00:28:40,885 --> 00:28:42,920
Duke?

527
00:28:48,427 --> 00:28:52,229
What the hell were you up to?

528
00:28:52,231 --> 00:28:55,466
But I don't understand
why your mom would paint these.

529
00:28:55,468 --> 00:28:57,801
I don't know either.

530
00:28:57,803 --> 00:29:01,505
Maybe way back then,
she knew the dome was coming.

531
00:29:01,507 --> 00:29:03,974
Or... The stars
are something

532
00:29:03,976 --> 00:29:06,510
That will happen
now that the dome is here.

533
00:29:06,512 --> 00:29:09,146
You think
she could see the future?

534
00:29:10,515 --> 00:29:13,117
If she did, then you can, too,
because you started talking

535
00:29:13,119 --> 00:29:15,252
About the pink stars
during your seizure.

536
00:29:15,254 --> 00:29:16,453
I-I was just babbling.

537
00:29:16,455 --> 00:29:19,990
And you saying it
was a coincidence?

538
00:29:19,992 --> 00:29:21,825
I don't know what to think.

539
00:29:21,827 --> 00:29:23,927
Yes, you do.

540
00:29:23,929 --> 00:29:26,430
You know I've been right
about this all along.

541
00:29:27,899 --> 00:29:30,000
I'm not crazy.

542
00:29:31,236 --> 00:29:34,037
And my mom wasn't either.
She knew something was coming.

543
00:29:34,039 --> 00:29:39,176
And... I must be part of it
because I'm in this painting.

544
00:29:41,112 --> 00:29:43,113
And now obviously
you're part of it, too.

545
00:29:44,415 --> 00:29:46,283
Don't you see how great that is?

546
00:29:46,285 --> 00:29:48,118
Great?

547
00:29:48,120 --> 00:29:50,053
How is any of this great?

548
00:29:50,055 --> 00:29:52,256
It's great
because we're in this together.

549
00:29:52,258 --> 00:29:56,894
I always loved you, angie.

550
00:29:56,896 --> 00:29:59,296
And now we're connected
through something even bigger

551
00:29:59,298 --> 00:30:01,331
And better than that.

552
00:30:07,005 --> 00:30:10,007
So... Now what?

553
00:30:10,009 --> 00:30:14,444
And tell her everything
was on the up-and-up after all.

554
00:30:14,446 --> 00:30:16,814
max:
Good job with the guns.

555
00:30:16,816 --> 00:30:19,483
Now, that is
what I call a success.

556
00:30:21,820 --> 00:30:23,287
Uh, you didn't have
to come by here.

557
00:30:23,289 --> 00:30:26,423
And miss the chance
to congratulate you in person?

558
00:30:30,195 --> 00:30:32,963
Since when did you turn down
a pat on the back?

559
00:30:32,965 --> 00:30:36,033
This is, uh,
dale barbara. He...

560
00:30:41,406 --> 00:30:44,942
Oh, barbie and I
know each other.

561
00:30:48,980 --> 00:30:50,914
Norrie:
That was a whole day wasted.

562
00:30:50,916 --> 00:30:53,917
Maybe we'll come up with a way
to find the mini-dome tomorrow.

563
00:30:53,919 --> 00:30:56,053
Hey, truman.
Where's your bowl?

564
00:30:56,055 --> 00:30:58,222
Let's get you fed.

565
00:30:58,224 --> 00:31:00,290
I'm gonna go
check on carolyn.
All right.

566
00:31:03,896 --> 00:31:05,395
Norrie:
what is it this time?

567
00:31:05,397 --> 00:31:07,598
A squirrel?
Probably a barn rat.

568
00:31:32,290 --> 00:31:34,358
♪

569
00:31:51,643 --> 00:31:53,610
You're not gonna say
anything to me, barbie?

570
00:31:53,612 --> 00:31:55,145
"long time no see"?

571
00:31:55,147 --> 00:31:58,115
"hey, you look great"?

572
00:31:58,117 --> 00:32:01,451
Hello, max.

573
00:32:01,453 --> 00:32:03,253
Anything to say to me?

574
00:32:03,255 --> 00:32:05,022
After claiming
all this time

575
00:32:05,024 --> 00:32:07,257
To be just a guy
passing through,

576
00:32:07,259 --> 00:32:10,193
Never been to chester's mill
or anywhere around here?

577
00:32:10,195 --> 00:32:11,962
Oh, kind of how you claimed that

578
00:32:11,964 --> 00:32:14,598
Collecting all these
was <i>your</i> idea? Because she

579
00:32:14,600 --> 00:32:16,199
Put you up to it.

580
00:32:16,201 --> 00:32:18,368
No, I did what's
best for this town.
Oh, yeah.

581
00:32:18,370 --> 00:32:20,570
Lying through your teeth
every step of the way.

582
00:32:20,572 --> 00:32:22,372
Girls, girls, girls,
you're both pretty.

583
00:32:22,374 --> 00:32:25,676
Which is why I'm cutting
you in on our plan
for chester's mill.

584
00:32:25,678 --> 00:32:29,513
Step one: Disarm the opposition.

585
00:32:29,515 --> 00:32:32,149
Hard times mean
desperate people.

586
00:32:32,151 --> 00:32:34,451
Especially in this
pressure cooker. And...

587
00:32:34,453 --> 00:32:36,119
Everything that
big jim said,
that was true.

588
00:32:36,121 --> 00:32:39,122
We only want people to
be safe and... Happy.

589
00:32:39,124 --> 00:32:41,525
Let me guess, next,
you're gonna give 'em a little

590
00:32:41,527 --> 00:32:44,995
Black market to occupy
their time, am I right?

591
00:32:44,997 --> 00:32:47,130
Huh? Some booze? Drugs?

592
00:32:47,132 --> 00:32:48,632
A little gambling?

593
00:32:48,634 --> 00:32:50,567
See? You have nothing
to worry about.

594
00:32:50,569 --> 00:32:54,037
Who the hell said that
I'm gonna help you?

595
00:32:54,039 --> 00:32:56,206
Who says you have a choice?

596
00:32:56,208 --> 00:32:59,276
You have quite a few secrets
buried in your past, barbie.

597
00:32:59,278 --> 00:33:01,078
I would hate for those secrets

598
00:33:01,080 --> 00:33:03,413
To get dug up
for <i>everyone</i> to see.

599
00:33:03,415 --> 00:33:07,284
Big jim:
Oh, please, please, dig 'em up.

600
00:33:07,286 --> 00:33:08,752
Careful what
<i>you</i> wish for, jimmy,

601
00:33:08,754 --> 00:33:11,054
Because while I'm digging,
I might accidentally reveal

602
00:33:11,056 --> 00:33:14,358
A few of the pies
you've got <i>your</i> fingers
stuck in around town.

603
00:33:16,227 --> 00:33:18,028
You both have been
working for me,

604
00:33:18,030 --> 00:33:19,629
Even if you didn't
know about each other,

605
00:33:19,631 --> 00:33:22,099
And now is not the time
to grow a conscience

606
00:33:22,101 --> 00:33:23,667
Unless you want to
face a jail cell.

607
00:33:23,669 --> 00:33:26,003
Or a lynch mob or...
Whatever it is

608
00:33:26,005 --> 00:33:28,271
That passes for justice
around here these days.

609
00:33:28,273 --> 00:33:31,241
You're not bulletproof, max.

610
00:33:31,243 --> 00:33:34,177
Which is why I have
an insurance policy in place.

611
00:33:34,179 --> 00:33:38,648
Anything bad happens to me,
your secrets still come out.

612
00:33:41,185 --> 00:33:43,020
All right.

613
00:33:43,022 --> 00:33:46,189
Like I said, great
job today. Jimmy,

614
00:33:46,191 --> 00:33:49,126
Make sure these get
loaded up and delivered
to the cement factory.

615
00:33:49,128 --> 00:33:51,395
Truck's waiting out back.

616
00:33:53,197 --> 00:33:55,699
Give her a kiss good-bye
for me, will you?

617
00:33:58,136 --> 00:34:00,103
Look at us.

618
00:34:01,139 --> 00:34:03,073
Back in business.

619
00:34:03,075 --> 00:34:06,043
And to think, it all
started...

620
00:34:06,045 --> 00:34:08,078
With you buying me
that drink,

621
00:34:08,080 --> 00:34:10,113
Oh, so many months ago.

622
00:34:10,115 --> 00:34:13,683
No, you bought <i>me</i> the drink.

623
00:34:13,685 --> 00:34:17,320
And then two days later,
we came up for air.

624
00:34:17,322 --> 00:34:19,723
Look, whatever
you and jim
are up to here,

625
00:34:19,725 --> 00:34:22,125
You are making
a huge mistake.

626
00:34:22,127 --> 00:34:23,660
And you're right
there with us.

627
00:34:23,662 --> 00:34:25,695
No, I don't think so.

628
00:34:28,099 --> 00:34:31,201
So... You
don't care if

629
00:34:31,203 --> 00:34:33,637
Julia shumway hears you
murdered her husband?

630
00:34:33,639 --> 00:34:35,839
E-excuse me?
Oh, please.

631
00:34:35,841 --> 00:34:38,175
You called me from
your car afterwards.

632
00:34:38,177 --> 00:34:40,310
You were frantic
because he fought back.

633
00:34:40,312 --> 00:34:42,112
And then I start
hearing rumors

634
00:34:42,114 --> 00:34:43,814
That dr. Shumway
has vanished.

635
00:34:43,816 --> 00:34:47,217
The pillow talk
between you and julia

636
00:34:47,219 --> 00:34:50,687
Is gonna be done when she finds
out you're the reason why.

637
00:34:52,490 --> 00:34:54,257
What?

638
00:34:54,259 --> 00:34:55,792
Oh.

639
00:34:55,794 --> 00:34:58,528
You're surprised that I know
you're screwing the widow, too?

640
00:35:00,198 --> 00:35:02,432
For the past eight days,
I've been watching you,

641
00:35:02,434 --> 00:35:05,402
And big jim, and everyone
in this hellhole.

642
00:35:06,571 --> 00:35:09,439
So keep that in mind
before you even <i>think</i>

643
00:35:09,441 --> 00:35:11,708
About opening
your big mouth.

644
00:35:15,480 --> 00:35:17,581
I can't believe
it's here.

645
00:35:17,583 --> 00:35:19,516
Yeah, and still...

646
00:35:19,518 --> 00:35:21,685
Doing whatever
the hell it does.

647
00:35:23,856 --> 00:35:27,157
That's what you found
in the woods, isn't it?

648
00:35:27,159 --> 00:35:29,392
What you started
to mention earlier?

649
00:35:29,394 --> 00:35:31,595
Yeah. Two days ago.

650
00:35:31,597 --> 00:35:34,197
And you're not
freaking out about it?

651
00:35:34,199 --> 00:35:35,732
Believe me, I want to.

652
00:35:35,734 --> 00:35:38,902
But I can't deny
that I'm a part of this now.

653
00:35:40,672 --> 00:35:42,706
And besides...

654
00:35:42,708 --> 00:35:44,841
It's kind of cool.
Norrie: It was
in the woods.

655
00:35:44,843 --> 00:35:46,209
How did it get here?

656
00:35:46,211 --> 00:35:47,611
Joe brought it.

657
00:35:47,613 --> 00:35:49,679
What are you
talking about?
Did you lie to me?

658
00:35:49,681 --> 00:35:51,581
No, I did not bring
that thing here.

659
00:35:51,583 --> 00:35:53,416
Joe, you don't remember
last night?

660
00:35:53,418 --> 00:35:54,584
What's there
to remember?

661
00:35:54,586 --> 00:35:56,720
I was in the kitchen
at, like, 3:00

662
00:35:56,722 --> 00:35:58,255
Getting something to drink,
and then you...

663
00:35:58,257 --> 00:36:01,625
Came down the stairs and
half scared me to death.

664
00:36:01,627 --> 00:36:04,227
I asked you what you were doing,
and you said that you were

665
00:36:04,229 --> 00:36:07,597
Going out on a walk all...
Zombie-like.

666
00:36:07,599 --> 00:36:09,699
And then you
just walked out.

667
00:36:09,701 --> 00:36:12,169
And you didn't stop me?

668
00:36:12,171 --> 00:36:13,937
I mean, didn't you think
that that was weird?

669
00:36:13,939 --> 00:36:15,438
Of course!

670
00:36:15,440 --> 00:36:17,440
But what isn't these days?

671
00:36:17,442 --> 00:36:19,809
Can't argue that.

672
00:36:19,811 --> 00:36:21,878
Okay.

673
00:36:23,181 --> 00:36:25,382
So I...

674
00:36:25,384 --> 00:36:27,751
Guess I was sleep-walking.

675
00:36:29,320 --> 00:36:32,556
But why did I bring
this thing here?

676
00:36:32,558 --> 00:36:34,791
Julia:
<i>But we couldn't find</i>
<i>the mini-dome anywhere.</i>

677
00:36:34,793 --> 00:36:38,595
I told them there has to be
a logical explanation

678
00:36:38,597 --> 00:36:40,430
For why it disappeared.

679
00:36:40,432 --> 00:36:43,833
I mean, this whole time
I have been holding on

680
00:36:43,835 --> 00:36:46,403
To the belief
that there is some...

681
00:36:46,405 --> 00:36:49,506
Explanation
for why this is happening.

682
00:36:49,508 --> 00:36:51,875
After today,
I don't know.

683
00:36:51,877 --> 00:36:54,211
Maybe we'll
never understand.

684
00:36:54,213 --> 00:36:57,647
: Maybe it's better
to just say screw it,

685
00:36:57,649 --> 00:37:00,717
And stop looking for answers
we're never gonna get.

686
00:37:07,391 --> 00:37:09,659
Be grateful
for what we do have.

687
00:37:13,731 --> 00:37:15,365
Right, yeah.

688
00:37:18,703 --> 00:37:21,438
You want to tell me
about your day?

689
00:37:25,509 --> 00:37:27,711
Nah, it can wait
till morning.

690
00:37:29,780 --> 00:37:31,414
Is that right?

691
00:37:31,416 --> 00:37:33,350
Mm-hmm.

692
00:37:33,352 --> 00:37:35,752
Well, do you want
to take me to bed?

693
00:37:45,730 --> 00:37:48,398
Actually, I'm gonna
stay up for a while.

694
00:37:50,968 --> 00:37:52,869
Yeah?
Yeah.

695
00:37:54,305 --> 00:37:56,306
Is everything okay?

696
00:37:56,308 --> 00:37:58,375
Yeah, it's fine.

697
00:37:59,677 --> 00:38:01,544
Fine.

698
00:38:06,617 --> 00:38:08,752
♪

699
00:39:11,749 --> 00:39:13,817
♪

700
00:39:26,897 --> 00:39:28,965
Well, maybe you brought it here

701
00:39:28,967 --> 00:39:31,434
'cause no one else
is allowed to see it.

702
00:39:31,436 --> 00:39:33,069
You think?
I don't know.

703
00:39:33,071 --> 00:39:35,739
But that time you
shushed the camera,
we thought the dome

704
00:39:35,741 --> 00:39:37,741
Was telling us not
to talk about our seizures.

705
00:39:37,743 --> 00:39:40,143
Okay, so maybe only
people who've had them

706
00:39:40,145 --> 00:39:41,811
Are supposed to
interact with it.

707
00:39:41,813 --> 00:39:43,847
Which means we
probably shouldn't tell julia

708
00:39:43,849 --> 00:39:45,749
That we found this again.

709
00:39:45,751 --> 00:39:47,417
Okay, but...

710
00:39:47,419 --> 00:39:50,553
Even if it's only
for us to know about,

711
00:39:50,555 --> 00:39:53,590
What do we do with it?

712
00:40:20,818 --> 00:40:23,586
Did it do this before?

713
00:40:24,555 --> 00:40:26,589
No.

714
00:40:26,591 --> 00:40:28,124
It's almost like...

715
00:40:28,126 --> 00:40:31,027
These are locks...

716
00:40:31,029 --> 00:40:34,431
And our hands are the keys.

717
00:40:39,837 --> 00:40:42,439
I think we need a fourth hand.

718
00:40:44,041 --> 00:40:45,975
I guess we need to find them.

